    • Method Detail

      • simpleWhiteSpaceTokenizer

        public String[] simpleWhiteSpaceTokenizer(String value)
        Splits a given string into tokens based on white space. This ignores quotation marks. So in a line like 
         The "dirty red" fish was here.

        the tokens would be

        • The
        • "dirty
        • red"
        • fish
        • was
        • here.
        Parameters:
        value - The String to be tokenized.
        Returns:
        an array of String containing the tokens of the value.

      • quotedWhiteSpaceTokenizer

        public String[] quotedWhiteSpaceTokenizer(String value)
        Splits a given string into tokens based on white space. This function recognizes quotation marks and any white space there contained is kept. So in a line like 
         The "dirty red" fish was here.

        the tokens would be

        • The
        • dirty red
        • fish
        • was
        • here.
        Parameters:
        value - the text line that should be split into tokens.
        Returns:
        an array of String containing the tokens of the value.

      • tokenizeWithPattern

        public String[] tokenizeWithPattern(String regexPattern,
                                    String value)
        Split the value string with a custom regex pattern. This method supports multiple groups in the regex pattern.
        Parameters:
        regexPattern - The RegEx pattern as String
        value - the value to be split by the RegEx pattern.
        Returns:
        an array of String containing the tokens of the value.
